{
  "stem": "1387.3",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "Bari was a large camp-- established camp.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And the survivors created drama clubs, soccer team, boxing teams-- all kinds of sports.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "There was an organizational [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] committee, and we were provided with most of our needs.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I-- I saw no evidence of that.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We were a few kilometers out of town-- out of town of Bari.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But I bought a Friedlander camera for about a few dollars-- $5-- and I were going every day to the beaches in Bari and taking pictures of--",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Holiday makers.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And developed them during the night with a young man as a partner by the name of Irving [?",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Mala, ?] and bring those pictures back to the beaches the next day and make money.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] We also were involved in some black marketeering, like the American soldiers [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] could not get rid of single dollars.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They wanted large-- larger--",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So they were selling those bills, those single-dollar bills and smaller denominations, for less than-- than big money.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we used to take that-- ride on a open train to Milano from Bari and sell it there for a few cents more.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And this is how we acquired some money.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Now, my traveling to Italy was intended to go to Palestine.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The political situation there was such, again, that the British closed the borders and opened a camp in-- in Cyprus.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And at that time, I decided that I'm not going to another camp, and I wrote a letter to my uncle-- my father's brother-- in the United States to send me papers.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "He sent me papers from HIAS-- through the HIAS-- and I applied to the American Embassy in Naples to come to America.",
      "word_count": 22
    }
  ],
